merchant_details.name: Hotel Avenida De Canarias Gran Canaria

reviews.excerpt:
This definitely is a secret escape. A real Hotel for workers and sportive open minded people at the center of Gran Canaria for any bike trips, hiking or surfing. Or a great place for intelectual people, to hang out with the working class. For cyclists, no Wind battle to come back in the evening and a lovely descend. 
Being a guest you are treated like a "family" member. The Hotel is a cooperativa, and people working there are warm hearted! Hardly to name only one person of this great "family" however I will do: Lourdes, is a great cook! and even it is hardly to improve that buffet, she is a even a better person, looking for everybody and trying to fulfill every wish. At this Hotel there is no touristic area or feeling, nor a swimming pool or any kind of these attractions. The attraction is the warm hearted way you are are treated, just being a kind of "family" member.
reviews.author: Emmanuel Winkler

reviews.excerpt: Comida mexicana auténtica. La comida está muy rica (al menos lo que pedimos) y de precios asequible. El problema del local es que es bastante pequeño en su interior, aunque cuentan con una terraza amplia en verano. Yo tengo que valorar nuestra experiencia en el interior del local y la verdad no me gustó, ya que nos pusieron justo al lado de la cocina y el calor era insoportable. Reservamos con varios días de antelación y es el sitio en el que nos pusieron, por lo que no me pareció correcto. Cogimos un cupón y nos regalaron unos margaritas. Lo único que habían eran unos ventiladores que me parecen insuficientes en verano. Todo el local está decorado al estilo cantina mexicana con sombreros y máscaras. En general, sensación agridulce.
reviews.author: Valentín Miguel Lozoya

reviews.excerpt: Buena vista,mala insonorización. Hacen fiestas por la noche en el restaurante hasta las tantas de la mañana con música que retumba en las paredes y se escucha perfectamente en el baño. Así,sin previo aviso. Al día siguiente nos esperaba un viaje de vuelta de 5 horas en coche. Me sentí furiosa cuando no pude pegar ojo hasta las 4 de la mañana. Decepción total, si quieres descansar no lo recomiendo. El dueño no dio la cara por ningún sitio, me parece una estafa,hay menos ruido en una cafetería. Eso sí, la camarera muy amable nos puso el desayuno al día siguiente y dio la cara por él. Me fui con ganas de escribir en el libro de reclamaciones.

Oh, and they don't speak much English, but it was easy enough to point to something on the menu.

reviews.excerpt:
I liked this place so much that I went there twice during my week long trip to Madrid. The secind time I took all my work friends there and they too loved it. Its always crowded but its worth the wait! The restairant has a very authentic and local vibe. 

The jamon and cheese plate as well as the chorizo was of very high quality and to top it off the deserts were just right! 

The egg preparations with fries are wonderful and the house wine is great too! 

A must visit when in Madrid!

reviews.excerpt: I can only say "wow" after having had lunch here last Sunday. No frills place but amazingly efficient and friendly service that went out of their way to please and help. Value for money, one of the best restaurants ever. Basically Catalan cuisine but with some international dishes like goulash or chicken curry that we did not taste. We had a very good lunch for 3, with lots of beer, for EUR 74. Two à la carte, 1 set menu which at EUR 10,50 was very good: gazpacho, ham and melon, pork schnitzel and two scoops of ice cream. À la carte: croquettes (amazing portion, delicious), BBQ'd iberico pork, fish terrine, and mixed fish and seafood platter (which at 18 EUR included three small prawns, some clams, mussels, some sardines, a chunk of hake, some monkfish...you can't get better value for money if you buy from your fishmonger and cook it). Honest, family-driven, well executed, true to its origins. Go there.
reviews.author: Xavier Sansó

reviews.excerpt:
Podríamos decir del Mesón los Perez que es una de las elecciones más fiables de la zona. Quizá a nuestro gusto, la carta peca de extensa, con ciertos platos que aportan poco. Tapas, rebanadas, huevos, crepes, enrollados, pescados, carnes, etc, que recuerdan aquello de que quien mucho abarca…  
En todo este “tótum revolútum” nos atreveríamos a recomendar las Milhojitas del Pastor. En cuanto a carnes (entiendo que estas quieren ser la especialidad de la casa), lo que hace, lo hace bien, sin excesos, como meson se entiende que no pretende más. 
Tiene una carta de vinos más que presentable, desde luego de la mejores (si no la merjor) de la zona del Carpena, con clásicos para no arriesgar y jóvenes propuestas. 
A nuestro gusto, de los sitios más fiables de la zona para no fallar. Lo que ofrece, te lo da. Buen servicio aun sin cumplir los cánones clásicos de la hostelería y una ambientación interior que al menos lo intenta.

reviews.excerpt:
We have been there on Friday during UK half term (week of last May Monday) and it was nearly empty. Most of rides were just going straight in without any wait and i don't think we had to wait more than 5 minutes anywhere.  Longest wait I remember was in queue for ice cream.

+
Place is reasonably clean.
Slides/Rides were fun for my 7years old son.
-
2 biggest rides were closed (Twister and Kamikaze - not mentioned on their web page ! )
I have not seen any waves (haven't waited for them in pool so maybe we missed  every occasion ? ) 
Too many smokers even for half empty Aqualand (that applies to whole Spain though) 
Complicated renting of security boxes (you have to return the key AND some silly paper you really do not need for anything)
Good few rides did not have height checker at their beginning and we have seen safeguards turning kids away without explanation. Imagine waiting half an hour in queue just to be told you can't go on some slide.
reviews.author: Jan Matis

reviews.excerpt:
Amazing day out.....after reading some of the reviews was a little skeptical, went at the start of Sept so only 3/4 full. €90 for the whole day out for me and my partner so a little expensive.  Went on a few rides then brought the fast past.. definitely worth the 10 euros each, didn't wait longer than 10 mins for a ride plus you can go straight back on after. Sun beds 4 euros each and lock box 10 plus 5 back when you give the key in. Food over priced 10 euros for a burger and chips - 12.50 for a pizza... take your own.. health and safety is spot on rides were great. Perfect for all ages. 

All in all great day out would highly recommend!
reviews.author: sam lambell

reviews.excerpt: Most of the slides were brilliant, but the 'Super Slalom' was very poor. The wait was about half an hour and the slide itself was very slow. A couple of the main slides were closed due to maintenence which was disappointing. The line to get into the place was VERY long and the clothes lockers were very small. But apart from that the water park was brilliant!
reviews.author: Harry Baird

reviews.excerpt: Best waterpark on the costa del sol.  Huge fun, nice set up and they even have a FastPass system if you want to jump the queues a bit.
reviews.author: Justin Aldridge

reviews.excerpt:
This water park was a horrible experience and I will never go back to it. Basically every ride sucks and some have the potential of hurting you, as happened to me on "Speed Race" where I came out with a bleeding elbow. 
Everything in this water park is drastically overpriced. Paying 28€ just to enter one would expect to get everything else besides the food for free, but one has to pay for everything, like the usage of lockers. They charge 10€ for that, of which 5 are in case you lose the key. They told us that everything would fit inside one locker, but they turned out to be so small, that only one persons belongings fitted. 
Most of the personell are really unfriendly and do not care about a clients concerns or requests.
On another note the water in some pools is disgusting with trash and sand floating in it.
All in all I really cannot recommend this water park to anyone.

reviews.excerpt:
Did not realise it was a gay hangout until you see the flag. What I'm saying is that it's not in your face. Only realised after wondering why so many guys were at this end and saw the flag..penny dropped then. 

Have to stress it's not gay only hangout! So couples and families still very welcome. 
Music choice was a bit weird and got a bit annoying, but you soon learn to block that out as we returned 4 times during our holiday as it was so well priced and this side of the beach was less packed. 
9 euros for 1 parasol and 2 loungers which is reasonable for days use. The old gentleman who gave us tickets was lovely and kept and eye on everything.

Clean toilets and clean beach! 
Friendly staff 
Safe enough to leave our stuff hanging while we took a dip.
Welcoming and good choice of food and drinks which was reasonably priced.

ONLY Downside - sun is blocked due to building behind but this only happens around 6 or 7pm by which time you are ready to head for dinner away from the beach.

reviews.excerpt:
Mal,muy mal funciona media markt.
Muy poco respeto con el cliente y con los usuarios.
Compré hace pocos días un frigorífico y una lavadora,quedaron que hoy día 02/08/16 me traerían los electrodomésticos,pedí que me lo trajeran por la mañana (de 9.00 a 15.00h) y no me lo han traído.
Esta noche a las 21.07h me han mandado un correo diciéndome que me lo envían mañana a entre las 15.00 a 20.00h.
No me han dado explicaciones ni pedido disculpas por el retraso y además de una manera arbitraria y prepotente me han cambiado el horario de entrega (lo pedì por la mañana y me lo quieren enviar por la tarde que me viene muy mal).
Por supuesto la compra me la cobraron desde el primer minuto.
Un cero patatero para media  media markt.
Actitud prepotente y chulesca.
reviews.author: Felix Garcia- Ortiz Frores

reviews.excerpt: Portátil Acer Aspire con un año y un mes no arranca,como está dentro de los 2 años de  garantía lo llevo a la tienda para su reparación, al cabo de las dos semana me dicen que está fuera de garantía por haber derramado líquido en el PC,  siendo esto TOTALMENTE INCIERTO y que genera un presupuesto de 261 €  si quiero repararlo, siendo la escusa perfecta para desentenderse del problema, para colmo cuando le indico que no acepto el presupuesto y que me devuelvan mi equipo, me dan un impreso para que firme en el que me indica que el presupuesto(que yo no he solicitado) y  por transporte asciende a la cantidad de 25 € mas IVA, que vuelvo a negarme a firmar. Al final me devuelven mi ordenador sin coste alguno pero sin arreglar. NO VOLVERÉ A COMPRAR EN MEDIA MARKT.

IKEA...¿Quién no conoce un Ikea? Pues este más o menos como todos. De vez en cuando en vez de correr una maratón me voy con mis hijas y mujer a este Ikea que es el que me pilla más cerca. Acabo destrozado.
Esta integrado en un gran centro comercial llamado Río Shopping. Puedes hacer el día aquí sin salir a respirar aire.
reviews.author: Miguel Darco

reviews.excerpt:
Un IKEA como otro cualquiera... Un p*** laberinto y para colmo, tienes que perderte luego en el almacén buscando lo que vas a comprar. Es su modelo de negocio, y les va estupendamente, pero yo lo aborrezco sobremanera. Si fuese por este motivo le daba 1 estrella...

Tiene buenos productos a buen precio, la verdad. Bueno, bonito, barato. Esto hace que suba a 3 estrellas...

El aparcamiento del centro comercial es otro laberinto, no se quien lo diseñaria (probablemente el mismo de IKEA). En los días de mucha afluencia (en invierno casi todos los días), se forman unas colas bastante molestas, aunque no es la M-30, claro.Del parking subterráneo de IKEA no puedo comentar porque no he bajado a las ''cavernas'' nunca. Finalmente, 2 estrellas...

Un último consejo si vais a IKEA: id con tiempo, relajados, sin prisa, si es la primera vez llevaos provisiones, podéis quedaros 2 días buscando la manera de salir. Además no hay cobertura en todo el local para poder pedir un equipo de rescate y extracción de la UME. Ya me olvidaba de este detalle de la cobertura, lo que hace que baje a 1 estrella...
reviews.author: Joaquín Melgar Narváez

reviews.excerpt: We visited Casa Amatller right after doing Batllo.  In our opinion Amatller was way more interesting.  the house, furniture, door knobs, window pulls are all designed by Josep Puig i Cadafalch so they are all in perfect harmony with each other.  It is nearly 100% original, including the furniture, books, art, and all.  It was created a couple of years before Casa Batllo which probably made Mr. Batllo jealous of the sweet house Mr Amatller had.  The tours are guided by real people rather than audio guide like Batllo.  And because it is fully furnished, and is way less famous which means 1/100th of the number of people, it is just more intimate, really engaging and fantastically fun.  If you like Modernisme at it's best, you must check out Casa Amatller!
reviews.author: Paul Van Metre

reviews.excerpt:
It's well worth a visit as it's a beautifully designed house with all the furniture preserved and placed around the house so as to reconstruct the original set up. And therefore it's possible to see how the owners lived and admire the house's beauty in full. You can even see the kitchen with it's original furniture (which today is a part of the downstairs cafe). 
Out of all the modernist houses I've visited in Barcelona I've probably enjoyed this one the most.
reviews.author: Anonimowy Użytkownik

reviews.excerpt: Like Paul Van Metre (review also published) I visited Casa Amatller  after seeing Casa Batllo, and was so pleased that I did.  Amatller is a great example of the time, and it was so interesting to see a complete house, with furniture, door knobs, window pulls etc all designed by Josep Puig i Cadafalch. I was the only one on my tour, so had a truly personal experience, and my tour guide was so interesting and engaging. It was lovely to be in a real home, and to feel as though I was getting a special private insight into the lives of the owner and his daughter. A hidden delight and highly recommended.
reviews.author: Jane Tait

reviews.excerpt: Pieces from actual furniture are still there! Amazing ceilings!!

reviews.excerpt:
Horrible.

SERVICIO PÉSIMO: Puedes llevarte 1 hora sentado que nadie se va a acercar a preguntar si queréis algo de beber. Cuando llegan algunas bebidas, sólo los refrescos, los amontonan delante de un comensal para que el se encargue de repartirlos (sin cobrar sueldo de camarero).

Traen bebidas equivocadas y les faltan otras y ponen cara de asombro.

Después de 1h y media traen 1 plato para 1 comensal, y los demás mirando hambrientos. 

Hay que levantarse a por el pan, a por la sal, y si se te acaban las cervezas aguantate porque ahí no aparece un camarero para ponerte otra.

COMIDA:

Horrosa: Albóndigas heladas, tomate incomible, carrillada mal hecha.
Carne dura, cordero reseco. NO HABÍA NADA BUENO. Increíble pero de 11 comensales ninguno estaba bien.

Protestas 1 vez a la camerara, otra vez al encargado, pero no confíes en que nada vaya a cambiar.

CONCLUSIÓN: Café mejor en otro lado, porque si no dormirás ahí.

Eso sí, ante todas esas quejas, al encargado sólo le importa que te hayas quejado del tomate.

It was the first mall in Las Palmas and still continues to be the most popular one.

The installations are top notch, well maintained and have kept expanding to make place to new tenants and free parking space. 

There you should expect to find most major apparel retailers, the electronic mega chain MediaMart, a full fledged Carrefour among many local franchises, Kids Space, Coffees, McDonalds a few restaurants and Cinema. 

Located just at the on of the end la Playa de las Canteras, right in front the city's Auditorium Alfredo Krauss.

reviews.excerpt:
Shopping heaven, under the sun.

The Centro Comercial Las Arenas is in Las Palmas, near the Auditorio Alfredo Kraus at the end of the Las Canteras beach.

To get there, you take the GC-2 towards Gáldar; you'll soon see signs to the C.C. on the right. Or you can take a bus: numbers 17, 25, 31, 35 and 47 all go there. 

If you go by car, there's a gigantic underground car park with free parking for 3 hours. But they didn't control it when we were there, and there was what looked like a pretty permanent sign at the car park exit which said "Don't put your ticket in the machine - just drive up to the barrier and it will open". Which it did.

TIP 1: remember the colour of the pillars where you parked your car

TIP 2: remember the name of the shops on either side of the car park exit when you get to the mall; otherwise you'll never find your way back in again!

This is a proper shopping centre, unlike the ones in the resorts. It is very big, and has 3 floors of shops, with all the well-known names, Spanish and international. There is an enormous hypermarket where you can stock up on things to take home at better prices than in the resorts.

In fact, everything in the centro is Canarian price, not Foreign Tourist price, so you'll see a big saving here.

There's also an excellent choice of places for a snack or a full-blown meal, and a multi-screen cinema.

At certain times of the year, there are themed activities here. At Christmas there was an ice rink. An ice rink in 23 degrees heat!

There's generally something for all the family to latch on to here, from bargain booze to lovely jewellery to the latest fashions to cut-price games for your X-Box.

..

reviews.excerpt:
Hemos ido varias veces y todas ellas maravillosas ya que, aunque nuestro hijo llora, la atención y delicadeza con la que se le trata es suficiente para detectar que son profesionales con experiencia en niños.

Hoy, sin embargo, hemos tenido la mala suerte de dar con una persona que de profesional no tenía absolutamente nada. Su nombre Sara y su “maña” con niños absolutamente nula. Mi hijo de 3 años ha rabiado y llorado, se va con el pelo lleno de trasquilones y varias heridas en el cuello por tijeras y maquinillas. Al terminar, y ante nuestra queja diciendo que no volveríamos más, la “peluquera” nos responde textualmente “esto es la ostia, ¿te crees que tu hijo llora por mi culpa?” 

Cortarle el pelo a un niño no es fácil, por eso lo llevamos a un sitio especializado en ello, y pagamos un importe determinado por hacerlo, sino lo llevaríamos a cualquier peluquería del barrio.

Evidentemente, no volveremos.

reviews.excerpt:
It is a medium-small sized shopping center, built around the Carrefour supermarket. As for the shops, they are generally nice: several cloths and shoes dealer, a couple of bars and a few fast-food dealers, an electronics shop (Euronics), a bookstore, etc.
The supermarket is OK. One can find products of all sorts, e.g. cloths, sportsware, car parts, detergents, food... However, compared to homologous wide-surface supermarkets in France, this one stands on the rather smallish side, so certain items are missing or available only seasonally. Among food, fresh fish and cold cuts are available with a broad choice and good quality. Bakery sucks. Prices are OK overall. Nice discounts, usually offered through a customer-loyalty program, make this supermarked one of the cheapest in Pavia. 2016 saw the introduction of a single line: it smoothed queuing out a bit, except at peak times.
The parking lot was planned oversize: it is never packed. On the other hand, one-ways make driving rather confusing and labyrinthine.

reviews.excerpt:
Esta en la zona media de lo que se puede encontrar en Islantilla. Situado en la planta superior del centro comercial de la Av. Islantilla. Tiene mesas en la terraza con vistas al mar. El servicio es eficiente y correcto. Pero, dependiendo de quien te toque son mas o menos amables. Pero nunca es un servicio malo. Como mucho seco. 

De entrantes unas gambas blancas con sal gorda. Buenas sin llegar a traspasar a muy buenas. Cazón, que fue lo peor, casi sin sabor. Como ese pescado congelado que siempre sabe mas a lo que le acompaña que a si mismo. Y choco que, aunque un poco duro, estaba bueno. 

Comimos un arroz con bogavante de plato principal. Muy generoso podrían haber comido más personas y, aunque el arroz tenia un buen punto, no estaba especialmente sabroso. Le faltaba contundencia al sabor. Correcto sin más. 

Un sitio al que se puede ir, pero no una primera opción. 

Como detalle no hay que dejar de tener en cuenta que son un poco caros

reviews.excerpt:
El trato del dueño es repugnante. Los que ya tenemos una edad y hemos pasado de ir de jovencitos a ir con nuestras familias no estamos para pagar 200 euros todos los días en la comida y que su dueño sin ningún estilo ni elegancia nos trate como al ganado.
Me paso al chiringuito del Meliá o el Albatros donde la puesta de sol es la misma, pero sin darte codazos para comer, cenar, y en los que puedes tomarte una copa sentado tranquilamente y puedes disfrutar de la conversación de tus acompañantes. En el Atenas no puedes.
En cualquier caso el sitio está lleno de gente joven, cosa de la que se jacta el dueño, sin agradecernos a los que con los 200 euros diarios le ayudamos a levantar su chiringuito.
Y una cosa más, esta zona de la playa se la esta cargando llenandola de gente con muy poco nivel que van al copeo borreguil de las seis de la tarde con la música a todo volumen que se oye desde las urbanizaciones del Novo.
Hay mucho mejores chiringuitos a poca distancia de este y con un ambiente mucho más cuidado.
reviews.author: mar rubio

reviews.subj: Review from José Antonio Junior García
reviews.excerpt: Obviamente el enclave es espectacular y el interior del restaurante frente al mar es fascinante. Lo que pasa es que el servicio en Agosto fue bastante regular tanto por despistes en las comandas, tardío e incluso el ticket final con errores. Todo comprensible por el mes de esta visita. La terraza de copas es muy comoda y bien servida. Felicidades por este complejo.

reviews.excerpt:
Chiringuito Atenas Playa - Chiclana
El chiringuito cuenta con una zona de hamacas y camas balinesas, con pasarelas entre las distintas filas de hamacas donde se ofrece servicio de restauración tanto de bebidas, comidas, cockteles y copas.
Anexo al chiringuito, en la propia arena de la playa, se encuentra una zona chilout donde poder disfrutar de buena música, tanto en mesas altas como en pufs y cojines de mojitos, cocteles, copas y toda la gastronomía que ofrecemos en el interior. 
Horario: Lunes a Domingo desde las 11:00 horas hasta las 02:30 horas.

La única pega y no es estrictamente del propio camping, si no de quien te toque de "vecino" de parcela, hay muchas personas que te rompen la experiencia no respetando los horarios de descanso, manteniendo televisiones, música y conversaciones a viva voz hasta muy altas horas de la madrugada, no todo el mundo sabe disfrutar de la experiencia de veranear en camping.

reviews.excerpt:
Esta mañana (24/08/2016) he acudido a por Nobritol con la correspondiente receta a esta farmacia. Por segunda vez en el año que llevo enferma, me han negado dicho fármaco por, supuestamente, no ser válida la receta. La misma había sido expedida por el especialista que me trata una hora antes en su consulta (en ella figuraba el nombre del medicamento, nombre del doctor, número de colegiado, dirección, teléfono de contacto, firma y sello). Tras cotejarlo con la Policía Nacional, he acudido a otra farmacia, en la C/ Sangenjo nº 29 y me han indicado que la receta era perfectamente válida, dispensándome dicho medicamento inmediatamente. 
Escribo esta reseña porque NO es fácil estar enfermo, ni acudir a comprar los medicamentos que palían los síntomas de tu enfermedad. Menos fácil es aún cuando te DISCRIMINAN por el tipo de medicamento que vas a comprar (llevando una receta perfectamente válida). Solo espero que si algún día las personas que atienden esta farmacia se ven en mi situación, den con profesionales de verdad que se preocupen por el bienestar de sus pacientes.

Mercadona is my favorite chain of supermarkets/grocery shops in Madrid. The prices are very good. The selection is perfect. They've got fresh fish, meats, cheeses,  and jamon for those who love it. 

The only down side of this place is that it's pretty small in comparison to other mercadonas I've been to. But nevertheless it's perfect for a quick fridge top off. I wouldn't go here  to pack a house from the ground up though. 

Oh and the veggies. The veggies and fruit section has got the essentials. Nothing fancy. 

Parking is free and shaded. It's never packed. Closes on Sundays.

Se li avessi saputo prima certamente non mi sarei fermato a cena e sarei andato altrove! Mi sono recato al McDonald's esclusivamente per il regalo promesso e con grande delusione.....anzi proprio incazzatura...abbiamo ricevuto con menefreghismo assoluto un bel 2 di picche!!!! I panini non sono cosi fantasmagorici e se dimenticano di dare ai bambini i regali promessi possono anche cambiare mestiere!!! Male male male e ancora male.....non tornerò mai più!!!

reviews.excerpt:
El Campus Sur de la Universidad Politécnica de Madrid lo componen las escuelas de ingenieros de telecomunicación,  topografía e informática. Está ubicada en Madrid, entre la A-3 (Autovía de Valencia) y la M-40, por lo que su acceso en coche es bastante accesible, además no hay problemas de aparcamiento. En transporte público se puede llegar desde Conde de Casal en el autobús universitario E, así como en metro y cercanías, aunque estos últimos están a 10 minutos a pie del campus. Comparte la biblioteca y el comedor entre otros servicios comunes. La biblioteca lleva muy pocos años construida y es excelente; dispone de WiFi, asientos y mesas muy adecuadas para el estudio, salas de reuniones, etc. y además abre todos los días del año. El comedor también es grande, y con un menú asequible. El campus también tiene instalaciones deportivas como pabellón polideportivo (gimnasio, baloncesto, volley playa...), y pistas de tenis y pádel.
Excelente biblioteca para estudiantes y opositores.

reviews.excerpt:
Esta biblioteca antes de nada hay que decir que para universitarios de la UPM, entre semana no suelen poner problemas pero en fin de semana piden el carnet.

También hay que avisar que desde los recortes ya no se puede quedar uno hasta las 10 solo dejan hasta las 9, tiene salas de estudio para trabajos en grupo donde ahora los fines de semana no se pueden utilizar y los libros solo se pueden coger y devolver entre semana, cosa que antes se podían devolver hasta en fin de semana.

la seguridad brilla por su ausencia dado que las mayoría están enfocadas a los edificios y no a las personas, las que hay en las entradas o no enfocan bien la entrada o están situadas de tan forma que casi si hay algún problema no graban nada puesto que o hay algún árbol tapando la visualización o hay ángulos muertos.

La velocidad dentro del campus no esta controlada y los conductores hacen giros 
prohibidos,van a velocidades indebidas, algunas veces ni respetan a los peatones, incluso llegan a pasar camiones y autobuses (no los de la EMT), los fines de semana la gente utiliza el campus para practicas de conducir con sus familiares y época de fiestas no te dejan disfrutar del propio césped aunque seas de la UPM y le quieras enseñar el carnet.

Factorías Vulcano es uno de los más importantes astilleros en España. Están especializados en la construcción de alto valor añadido nuevas construcciones de tamaño medio, que oscilan entre 80 y 170 m de longitud. Y lo hacen para algunos de los más exigentes armadores y comercializa en el mundo. A cabo la empresa se remonta a 1919, aunque su actividad en el negocio de la construcción naval comenzó en 1940. En línea con la mayoría de los europeos empresas de este sector, la empresa ha evolucionado progresivamente hacia su modelo actual "síntesis astillero".
  
Factorías Vulcano is one of the most important shipyards in Spain. We are specialised in the construction of high added value mid-sized newbuildings, ranging between 80 and 170 m in length. And we do so for some of the most demanding ship-owners and markets in the world. Out company harks back to 1919, although its activity in the shipbuilding business began in 1940. reviews.excerpt:
DO NOT BOOK THIS HOTEL!!!!!

We were extremely disappointed to learn that this hotel appear to possibly be run by management which policy is to trick you out of as much money as possible. 
 
All staff seemed to be well versed in what to tell customers and appeared VERY used to receiving similar complaints as my own. 

The Story: 
We were told that our booking was not flexible when we asked to change our booking from 9th to 8th (or cancel) a few weeks prior to arrival (despite most hotels offering a total cancellation policy, even the day before arrival!)  In addition, we were told all family rooms were booked up and we needed to book two double rooms - at twice the cost of course, for the 8th.  We only booked this hotel as we arrived late and near the airport, but accidentally booked it for wrong date. It's located by motorways in the middle of nowhere so we didn't want to hang around more than a night. 

When we arrived late in the evening, the porter at the reception mentioned a sofa-bed that could be pulled out, but quickly withdrew his comments when we wanted to know more. 

The next day we moved to our family room that we booked originally for 9th, ONLY TO DISCOVER THAT THE FAMILY ROOM WAS IN FACT IDENTICAL TO THE FIRST ROOM THAT WE WERE TOLD WAS A DOUBLE ROOM, it just had the sofa-bed pulled out ready to sleep in rather than folded in.  I instantly went down to reception to raise this issue, and was very surprised at how the staff dealt with it.  

The chap at reception barely batted an eye lid. He said if i'm not happy with the room blah blah blah.  I reiterated that i wasn't complaining about the room, I was unhappy that we had been tricked into paying for TWO rooms for the first night, when the hotel was firstly obviously a) not fully booked as they had said and b) the family room and the double room is the same. The chap still gave me his well versed story (as he continued with his paper filing and stapling) about how the rooms may look identical but in fact weren't (but no matter how much i tried to get an explanation, he didn't elaborate on how!).  He appeared neither surprised of my comments or had any inclination of wanting to explain. To me, it seemed that they say this to customers every day all day. Eventually, he said 'anyway you're actually lucky because on the second night you're paying less'.  Either having no braincells whatsoever as I had fully explained why were have had to book the first night there in any event, or, as i suspect, had been told so say this as part of their versed reply. When I asked to see the manager, he pretended to do the act of walking into a back office, but lingered at the door and instead the girl next to him behind the reception appeared, repeating again that I was lucky because on my second night (that I didn't want if you remember) i paid less. All seeming a very well versed act.  She also said that the first room did NOT have a sofa bed just a sofa.  I told them that in fact the porter on duty on our first night had actually owned up to the fact that it did INDEED have a sofa bed, but the reply i got was the same rehearsed reply, and explanation which in fact didn't quite fit in with my particular unique circumstances, but i guess if you don't have a real explanation (being - we lied to you to get more money out of you) then you go with what you've been told to say.

reviews.excerpt:
Un vivero en pleno centro de Valencia. 

Este tipo de negocio siempre está fuera de las ciudades. De hecho, ya hay un Verdecora en la carretera de Ademuz, muy cerca de muchas urbanizaciones.  Es muy raro encontrárselas dentro de la ciudad y aun menos en el centro. 

Está distribuida muy similar a las anteriores y la verdad es que es un local muy amplio. Los precios son similares y si que es verdad que está mas enfocado a plantas ornamentales para un "piso". Falta la variedad de arbustos que te puedes encontrar en la otra tienda.  Por otro lado, lógico. 

Lo que todavía no tienen en funcionamiento (al menos hasta el fin de semana pasado) es toda la parte de tiendas de animales, pero si la de accesorios para los mismos.

reviews.excerpt:
Did not realise it was a gay hangout until you see the flag. What I'm saying is that it's not in your face. Only realised after wondering why so many guys were at this end and saw the flag..penny dropped then. 

Have to stress it's not gay only hangout! So couples and families still very welcome. 
Music choice was a bit weird and got a bit annoying, but you soon learn to block that out as we returned 4 times during our holiday as it was so well priced and this side of the beach was less packed. 
9 euros for 1 parasol and 2 loungers which is reasonable for days use. The old gentleman who gave us tickets was lovely and kept and eye on everything.

Clean toilets and clean beach! 
Friendly staff 
Safe enough to leave our stuff hanging while we took a dip.
Welcoming and good choice of food and drinks which was reasonably priced.

ONLY Downside - sun is blocked due to building behind but this only happens around 6 or 7pm by which time you are ready to head for dinner away from the beach.

reviews.excerpt:
It's in the Thai style of Siam park, and I couldn't find fault with it. There's something for everyone there and didn't see any of the over inflated prices of some of the other shipping centres. Definitely worth a visit.
 I've seen the stupid reviews based on the fact that a woman opened a box of perfume and started spraying it round when there's no tester? She got bent out of shape because perfume expensive and she's spraying it round like a can of lynx(axe) and it's probably worth €100+, 2* ???? Get over yourself! The mall is made up of over 50+ different stores over 2 stories, there's a kids area with a gymcana similar to go-ape in the UK and around 7 or so bars/resturants which are fantastic, while we were there there were teens belting out operatic classis on the stage and I'm told there are other bands playing here. Last but not least there's a hyper Dino supermarket on the floor above the underground parking which is far better value than anything else within 4-5km. Well worth a visit to the Lizarran for some tapas and beers, or Toni Roma for a Tex Mex/Americano

La chica nos dijo que sólo podíamos pedir hamburguesa o sandwich sin darnos elección a nada más. Las hamburguesas estaban poco hechas y el pan durísimo, no se podía comer, además no sacaron platos para las hamburguesas teniendo que dejarlas en la servilleta mientras bebíamos. Nos quedamos con muy mal sabor de boca y por 12 euros por cabeza esa comida no valió la pena. Para rematar al final nos sacaron 10 chupitos para las 21 personas que eramos, un desastre.

reviews.excerpt:
We went there because Lonely Planet gave this place such a rave review and we so want to try the local specialty (roasted pig). Saw there fixed menu at the door (for 31 euros). We don't speak Spanish and guessed this menu was for two people. After we sat, a really weird waiter came here and apparently he spoke no English at all (that's okay with us), the problem is he didn't seem to want to learn what we want AT ALL! He took the menu away and just stood in a remote place. I had to go up to him (after 5 minutes sitting there wondering what's going on) and asked if we can order. He pointed me to another waiter. This one told me the menu we saw was meant for 1 people and said me another menu (with Spanish only, no English) and told me this was for 2 person.  His English was very limited, but he kept saying "this is for 2, not 1". So we ordered this. I have to say the roasted pig was good, but all other food were inferior to what we had had in Madrid. IMPORTANT thing is the portion of the food was like they were to feed birds. We asked the waiter again, and he said "this is for 2". Wondering if Europeans just eat small portion, we finished the meal and the second story came. I found a dead mosquito in my wine glass. It was just there after must of the wine was drunk. I called for the first waiter (who''d being waiting on us and all he could say was "done?") He looked at the dead mosquito and SAID NOTHING, just gave me another glass and took the dirty one away! We asked to talk with the waiter who recommended the menu (who can speak English) and told him the mosquito story. Suddenly, he couldn't understand English at all, just kept asking me" what? more wine?" and went away.  We were furious at that point and managed to find someone who spoke Spanish to translate our complaint to him. He said: well, the wine is drunk, what else do you want? another bottle? and he didn't look apologetic at all. So we just want to get out of this place asap, and when the ticket came, I found the meal we ate WAS EXACTLY WHAT I SAW AT THE DOOR (the set menu for 1 person!). Unable to bear this anymore, I asked the waiter why he gave meal for 1 when he told me this was for 2. You know what? He said "I told you this was for 1, not 2". During the whole process, all other waiters and the chef were just pretending they couldn't understand English so why bother. Other than "I told you this was for 1 person", the waiter said everything in Spanish, just to bug me off. 

I am really disappointed and humiliated by this place. We (young couple) are Asian and  live in U.S. . This is our first trip to Spain. Before this casa duque episode, we were so in love with Spain. It's good, people and culture. After being treated like this by such a "famous" place, we are not so sure about exploring.

Lo que por teléfono fué una reserva PARA las 15:30 se convirtió al llegar allí en una reserva A PARTIR de las 15.30 (obviamente de esta forma no hubiese ido). Gestión lamentable de la situación, donde había más gente que restaurante, pasando gente aleatoriamente mientras otra con reserva para antes se quedaba fuera. 
Teniendo en cuenta los precios, la comida muy corriente, el restaurante es bonito, eso sí, y el trato el peor que he recibido en toda mi vida. De hoja de reclamaciones.
No lo recomiendo en NINGUNA circunstancia.

No les importa que sigas metiendo la compra en la bolsa, porque atenderán al siguiente cliente, amontonando la compra de ambos. A mí ya me la pela y lo hago con total tranquilidad.

reviews.excerpt:
Acquisto slider monopattino a 3 ruote incompleto.
Ho acquistato un monopattino a 3 ruote e, tornato a casa per montarlo (scatola non sigillata), mancavano i ferma filo del freno cioè i due morsetti per i cavi del freno e due viti che sostengono una pedana. Quindi assemblaggio approssimativo e controllo da parte el personale inestistente.
Anche la bici da €  199,00 acquistata la stessa sera, peccava in assemblaggio: ho dovuto montare il campanello e regolare dei bulloni. Consiglio di verificare sempre la merce, anche se i dipendenti non acconsentono; altrimenti sconsiglio acquisti.
Giuseppe
